Greek banks that underwent European
Union stress tests are secure, with their Core Tier 1 capital
ratio at 2.44 billion euros ($3.43 billion) above the 5 percent
minimum required under the adverse scenario,  Kathimerini 
newspaper said, citing European Banking Authority Chairman
